  "title": "ELECTRICAL FITTER",
  "description": "<ul><li>C<a href=\"https://www.tafensw.edu.au/course-areas/electrotechnology/courses/certificate-ii-in-electrotechnology-career-start--UEE22020-01\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ertificate II in Electrotechnology</a></li><li>Installing, maintaining, and repairing electrical control, wiring, and lighting systems.</li><li>Reading technical diagrams and blueprints.</li><li>Performing general electrical maintenance.</li><li>Inspecting transformers, circuit breakers, and other electrical components.</li><li>Troubleshooting electrical issues using appropriate testing devices.</li><li>Repairing and replacing equipment, electrical wiring, and fixtures.</li><li>Following National Electrical Code state and local building regulations.</li><li>Performing circuit breaker corrective maintenance.</li><li>Maintaining good knowledge of heating and air conditioning systems as well as various testing equipment.</li><li>Problem solve on magnetic and electromagnetic devices, single path circuits, low voltage a.c. circuits, direct current machines and multiple path circuits</li><li>Fit, assemble, erect, manufacture, operate, test, fault find, repair and alter electrical equipment</li><li>Apply environmental and sustainable practices</li><li>Follow work health and safety practices</li></ul>",
